The paper deals with model-based diagnosis, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed methods involve heuristic search algorithms, which are commonly used in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of logical reasoners, which are often used in software engineering (cs.SE) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper proposes a new approach that is independent of the complexity of the diagnosed system, which could be relevant to programming languages and compilers (cs.PL).
